# Backend Development Rules

## Directory Structure

```
backend/
├── api/           # External API integrations
├── controllers/   # Request handlers (business logic)
├── middleware/    # Express middleware
├── models/        # Mongoose schemas
├── routes/        # API route definitions
├── scripts/       # Data fetching scripts
├── tests/         # Integration tests
├── utils/         # Utility functions
└── server.js      # Application entry
```

## Adding New API Endpoints

### Step 1: Create Route

```javascript
// backend/routes/newFeature.js
const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router();
const { handler } = require('../controllers/newFeatureController');

/**
 * @route GET /api/new-feature
 * @desc Description of endpoint
 * @access Public
 */
router.get('/', handler);

module.exports = router;
```

### Step 2: Create Controller

```javascript
// backend/controllers/newFeatureController.js

/**
 * Handler description
 * GET /api/new-feature
 * 
 * @see {@link docs/API_REFERENCE.md#new-feature} for API documentation
 */
const handler = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    // Implementation
    res.json({ success: true, data: {} });
  } catch (error) {
    next(error);
  }
};

module.exports = { handler };
```

### Step 3: Register Route in server.js

```javascript
app.use('/api/new-feature', require('./routes/newFeature'));
```

### Step 4: Add Tests

```javascript
// backend/controllers/__tests__/newFeatureController.test.js
// Follow testing conventions in docs/TESTING.md
```

### Step 5: Update Documentation

- Add endpoint to `docs/API_REFERENCE.md`
- Update `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` if needed

## Mongoose Model Template

```javascript
// backend/models/NewModel.js
const mongoose = require('mongoose');

/**
 * NewModel Schema
 * @see {@link docs/backend/models/NewModel.md} for documentation
 */
const newModelSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  field: {
    type: String,
    required: true,
  },
  createdAt: {
    type: Date,
    default: Date.now,
  },
});

// Indexes
newModelSchema.index({ field: 1 });

module.exports = mongoose.model('NewModel', newModelSchema);
```

## Utility Function Template

```javascript
// backend/utils/newUtil.js

/**
 * Utility function description
 * 
 * @param {Type} param - Description
 * @returns {ReturnType} Description
 * 
 * @example
 * const result = utilFunction(input);
 * 
 * @see {@link docs/backend/utils/newUtil.md} for documentation
 */
function utilFunction(param) {
  // Implementation
}

module.exports = { utilFunction };
```

## Error Handling

Always use try-catch and pass errors to next():

```javascript
const handler = async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    // Implementation
  } catch (error) {
    next(error); // Handled by middleware/errorHandler.js
  }
};
```

## External API Integration

When adding new external API:

1. Create file in `backend/api/`
2. Document API details (base URL, auth, rate limits)
3. Add caching if appropriate
4. Add tests in `backend/api/__tests__/`

## Environment Variables

Document new env vars in:
- `.env.example` (create if doesn't exist)
- `docs/backend/README.md`

## Testing Checklist

- [ ] Unit tests for controller functions
- [ ] Edge case tests (null, empty, error)
- [ ] Mock external dependencies
- [ ] Test file in `__tests__/` folder next to source
